              <h2>Purpose of this Policy</h2>
              <p>Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy policy provides an overview of how Triumph Int. (Cyprus) Limited ("{{config('app.name')}}") processes your personal data. We value the relationship that we have built with you and we place a very high priority safeguarding the data that you have provided to us.</p>
              <p>The processing of your personal data by {{config('app.name')}} must be in compliance with the provisions of applicable personal data protection law (including the EU General Data Protection Regulation or "GDPR").</p>
              <p>This privacy notice describes the kinds of personal and financial information pertaining to you that is collected by {{config('app.name')}} when you choose to use our services, how this will be used, when and with whom we share it and how we will keep it safe. The rights provided to you by the GDPR in relation to the processing of your personal data by us are similarly described in this policy.</p>
              <p>By accessing any {{config('app.name')}} website, including using any of the communication channels to contact us, we consider that you have read and understood the terms of this notice and how we process any information you disclose to us including personal data prior to becoming a client.</p>
              <p>By opening an account at any {{config('app.name')}} website, you agree that this notice, including any amendments will govern how we collect, store, use, share and in any other form process your personal data and your rights during our business relationship and after its termination.</p>
